The paper deals with a problem of influence diffusion in social networks, which is a topic of interest in the field of social informatics (cs.SI). The problem involves finding a small subset of nodes that can influence the whole network, which is a graph optimization problem and falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the application of the algorithm to real-life networks, which suggests a focus on social networks (cs.SOC). Additionally, the paper presents a fast and effective algorithm, which could be related to computer engineering (cs.CE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
